1
00:01:48,180 --> 00:01:49,740
I can do it.

2
00:01:49,780 --> 00:01:50,740
Go away.

3
00:01:50,780 --> 00:01:51,980
Hey.

4
00:01:52,020 --> 00:01:54,700
No, you...
leave me alone.

5
00:01:54,740 --> 00:01:55,980
Come on, come on, come on.

6
00:01:56,020 --> 00:01:57,100
Get off!

7
00:01:57,140 --> 00:01:58,380
I'm going to do it.
I'm going to it.

8
00:01:58,420 --> 00:01:59,380
Gonna do, do, do it.

9
00:01:59,420 --> 00:02:00,580
You're just cheating now.

10
00:02:00,620 --> 00:02:01,620
No, I'm not.
I can win this.

11
00:02:01,660 --> 00:02:03,500
Not you.
You're a loser.

12
00:02:03,540 --> 00:02:04,500
Ugh.

13
00:02:04,540 --> 00:02:07,420
Goal!

14
00:02:07,460 --> 00:02:08,620
Goal!

15
00:02:08,660 --> 00:02:09,620
Yes!

16
00:02:09,660 --> 00:02:10,700
How about it?

17
00:02:10,740 --> 00:02:12,060
Shall we play another game?

18
00:02:12,100 --> 00:02:14,460
I'm sick of you
and your childish games.

19
00:02:14,500 --> 00:02:15,780
You're just scared of losing.

20
00:02:15,820 --> 00:02:17,060
Come on.

21
00:02:17,100 --> 00:02:18,180
No.

22
00:02:19,500 --> 00:02:21,700
I'll just play by myself.

23
00:02:30,900 --> 00:02:32,300
<i># Looking back on days #</i>

24
00:02:32,340 --> 00:02:33,980
<i># And speaking up for more #</i>

25
00:02:34,020 --> 00:02:37,420
<i>#'Cause lights go down
as people get wiser #</i>

26
00:02:37,460 --> 00:02:40,700
<i># Just remember #</i>

27
00:02:49,700 --> 00:02:51,380
<i># In the nighttime #</i>

28
00:02:51,420 --> 00:02:52,900
<i># It's the right time #</i>

29
00:02:52,940 --> 00:02:55,700
<i># As the ceiling
hits the floor #</i>

30
00:02:55,740 --> 00:02:57,260
<i># It's the season #</i>

31
00:02:57,300 --> 00:02:59,020
<i># I got no reasons #</i>

32
00:02:59,060 --> 00:03:03,020
<i># Are you feeling insecure? #</i>

33
00:03:29,820 --> 00:03:31,780
Uh-huh.

34
00:03:31,820 --> 00:03:33,460
Yeah.

35
00:03:33,500 --> 00:03:36,460
Well, look, I'm just getting
through the door.

36
00:03:36,500 --> 00:03:38,220
So, yeah, if you just give me
five minutes,

37
00:03:38,260 --> 00:03:39,780
I can email it to you.

38
00:03:39,820 --> 00:03:41,940
Okay.

39
00:03:41,980 --> 00:03:43,380
Yeah, okay. Bye.

40
00:03:43,380 --> 00:03:44,340
Hi, love.

41
00:03:44,380 --> 00:03:45,540
Hey.

42
00:03:45,580 --> 00:03:46,860
Finish the article?

43
00:03:46,900 --> 00:03:47,860
More or less.
And you?

44
00:03:47,900 --> 00:03:49,420
So-so.

45
00:03:49,460 --> 00:03:51,340
We still need more tests
for the new drug.

46
00:03:51,380 --> 00:03:52,340
More tests?

47
00:03:52,380 --> 00:03:53,700
Poor little guinea pigs.

48
00:03:56,500 --> 00:03:58,460
Done your homework, you two?

49
00:03:58,500 --> 00:04:00,140
- Yes.
- Mm.

50
00:04:00,180 --> 00:04:01,940
How's the hand?
Does it still hurt?

51
00:04:04,420 --> 00:04:05,700
Are we still sulking?

52
00:04:05,740 --> 00:04:07,340
What's the problem?

53
00:04:07,380 --> 00:04:09,540
It's because of that concert
she wants to go to in London.

54
00:04:09,580 --> 00:04:12,180
Emma, I've already
told you once.

55
00:04:12,220 --> 00:04:15,020
That evening, I have to stay
late at the lab,

56
00:04:15,060 --> 00:04:16,780
and your father has a meeting
at the magazine.

57
00:04:16,820 --> 00:04:18,420
We need you
to take care of Mark.

58
00:04:18,460 --> 00:04:20,060
Again?

59
00:04:20,100 --> 00:04:21,380
Yes, again.

60
00:04:21,420 --> 00:04:22,580
I can take care myself.

61
00:04:22,620 --> 00:04:24,180
That's enough of that,
thank you.

62
00:04:24,220 --> 00:04:26,260
Besides, you're still too young
to be going to concerts.

63
00:04:26,300 --> 00:04:27,420
Alex and Rose are going,

64
00:04:27,460 --> 00:04:28,820
and they're nearly
the same age as me.

65
00:04:28,860 --> 00:04:30,940
Two years older is not
"nearly the same age."

66
00:04:30,980 --> 00:04:33,060
You know, instead of thinking
about going out so much,

67
00:04:33,100 --> 00:04:34,700
you should try
studying a bit more.

68
00:04:34,740 --> 00:04:36,300
I don't care
what your cousins are up to.

69
00:04:36,340 --> 00:04:38,300
I know what's best
for you, okay?

70
00:04:38,340 --> 00:04:39,820
But, Dad...

71
00:04:41,100 --> 00:04:43,380
You know what,
you never let me do what I want!

72
00:04:43,420 --> 00:04:44,740
Yes! Got it!

73
00:04:44,780 --> 00:04:47,460
Please stop playing
with that game?

74
00:04:47,500 --> 00:04:49,060
Emma, stop shouting.

75
00:04:49,100 --> 00:04:51,500
You know, if you want something
just say.

76
00:04:51,540 --> 00:04:54,300
Stop bawling
like a five-year-old.

77
00:05:05,260 --> 00:05:06,780
<i>I thought their heads
had dropped</i>

78
00:05:06,820 --> 00:05:09,260
<i>and they'd conceded,
but they've come back strongly.</i>

79
00:05:09,300 --> 00:05:10,860
<i>Penalized for that challenge.</i>

80
00:05:12,140 --> 00:05:14,220
Emma!

81
00:05:14,260 --> 00:05:15,180
Emma.

82
00:05:18,580 --> 00:05:19,500
Lucy!

83
00:05:21,140 --> 00:05:22,300
I don't know what's happening.

84
00:05:22,340 --> 00:05:24,220
Call an ambulance.

85
00:05:24,260 --> 00:05:25,220
Come on, quick!

86
00:05:29,020 --> 00:05:31,100
Um, yeah.
I need an ambulance.

87
00:05:31,140 --> 00:05:32,940
My daughter, she's having
a fit or something.

88
00:05:32,980 --> 00:05:34,700
Yeah.

89
00:05:34,740 --> 00:05:36,300
Emma Evans.

90
00:06:55,580 --> 00:06:57,380
Mum.

91
00:06:57,420 --> 00:06:59,580
Have you and Dad
had a chat yet about

92
00:06:59,620 --> 00:07:00,980
what we said
about secondary school?

93
00:07:01,020 --> 00:07:02,500
Yes.

94
00:07:02,540 --> 00:07:05,020
And?

95
00:07:05,060 --> 00:07:07,940
We both think
it's still too soon.

96
00:07:07,980 --> 00:07:09,260
Probably next year.

97
00:07:09,300 --> 00:07:11,420
But for the moment,

98
00:07:11,460 --> 00:07:13,140
the important thing is
that you get better.

99
00:07:13,180 --> 00:07:14,700
Okay?

100
00:07:21,900 --> 00:07:23,500
Hey.

101
00:07:24,620 --> 00:07:26,620
How's my favorite sister?

102
00:07:26,660 --> 00:07:27,620
Mm.

103
00:07:27,660 --> 00:07:31,500
So... any news?

104
00:07:31,540 --> 00:07:33,180
No. John's talking
to the doctor now.

105
00:07:33,220 --> 00:07:35,980
Oh, here's Dad now.

106
00:07:37,460 --> 00:07:39,860
Hi, Chris.

107
00:07:39,900 --> 00:07:42,180
Well, it's good news.

108
00:07:42,220 --> 00:07:44,820
All the tests
have turned out negative.

109
00:07:44,860 --> 00:07:46,380
Hmm?

110
00:07:46,420 --> 00:07:47,620
And?

111
00:07:47,660 --> 00:07:49,300
I find this incredible,
but they don't seem

112
00:07:49,340 --> 00:07:51,700
to have the slightest idea
what caused the attack.

113
00:07:51,740 --> 00:07:53,260
So what are we
supposed to do?

114
00:07:53,300 --> 00:07:54,940
Nothing.

115
00:07:54,980 --> 00:07:57,780
Just wait and hope
it doesn't happen again.

116
00:07:57,780 --> 00:07:59,220
And how are you feeling, Em?

117
00:08:01,420 --> 00:08:03,060
Emma.

118
00:08:04,260 --> 00:08:05,260
I'm fine.

119
00:08:05,300 --> 00:08:06,740
Don't worry.

120
00:08:06,780 --> 00:08:09,500
God won't let anything bad
happen to you.

121
00:08:13,100 --> 00:08:14,700
I'm going to get
another drink.

122
00:08:17,780 --> 00:08:19,060
Chris.

123
00:08:19,100 --> 00:08:20,620
I know Emma's been
to see you

124
00:08:20,660 --> 00:08:22,260
several times this year,
hasn't she?

125
00:08:22,300 --> 00:08:24,140
Yeah, she helps me out
in the canteen.

126
00:08:24,180 --> 00:08:25,420
Why?

127
00:08:25,460 --> 00:08:28,420
Has she ever said that she was
depressed about anything?

128
00:08:28,460 --> 00:08:30,700
She's a teenager.

129
00:08:30,740 --> 00:08:33,060
She just wants to go to school
like everyone else.

130
00:08:33,100 --> 00:08:35,860
But... you know that.

131
00:08:52,700 --> 00:08:56,420
Lucy, maybe we're making
a big mistake.

132
00:08:56,460 --> 00:08:58,100
What do you mean?

133
00:08:58,140 --> 00:08:59,540
It's only natural
that Emma wants

134
00:08:59,580 --> 00:09:00,900
to be with kids her own age.

135
00:09:00,940 --> 00:09:03,820
Oh, John, we've talked
about this over and over again.

136
00:09:03,860 --> 00:09:06,420
You know the statistics
as well as I do.

137
00:09:06,460 --> 00:09:09,580
Kids who study at home start
college much better.

138
00:09:09,620 --> 00:09:13,580
Emma isn't a statistic, Lucy.

139
00:09:13,620 --> 00:09:15,180
She's our daughter.

140
00:09:15,220 --> 00:09:17,220
And she is just... she's just
not happy at the moment.

141
00:09:17,260 --> 00:09:18,660
When she's older,

142
00:09:18,700 --> 00:09:20,780
she'll thank us for everything
we're doing for her.

143
00:09:20,820 --> 00:09:22,380
You'll see.

144
00:09:33,380 --> 00:09:35,020
<i>Drive safely, darling.</i>

145
00:09:35,060 --> 00:09:36,060
<i>Do you hear me?</i>

146
00:09:36,100 --> 00:09:37,820
<i>Yes, Mum.
Don't worry.</i>

147
00:09:48,340 --> 00:09:49,700
Hi.

148
00:09:49,740 --> 00:09:50,660
Hey.

149
00:09:50,740 --> 00:09:52,140
How'd you get on
at the doctor's?

150
00:09:52,180 --> 00:09:53,660
Fine.
It was nothing in the end.

151
00:09:53,700 --> 00:09:56,020
- Great. That's good news.
- Hi, Emma.

152
00:09:56,060 --> 00:09:58,020
Hi, Auntie.

153
00:09:59,540 --> 00:10:01,620
You missed one
hell of a gig, Emma.

154
00:10:01,660 --> 00:10:04,420
So shit they wouldn't
let you come.

155
00:10:04,460 --> 00:10:06,140
Your parents just need
to chill out.

156
00:10:06,180 --> 00:10:09,020
Are you okay?

157
00:10:09,060 --> 00:10:10,620
Sorry.

158
00:10:10,660 --> 00:10:12,500
My mum's crazy.

159
00:10:12,540 --> 00:10:13,860
She treats me as if I'm
the same age

160
00:10:13,900 --> 00:10:15,620
as my spoilt brother.

161
00:10:15,660 --> 00:10:18,620
Well, you two, I'm off.

162
00:10:18,660 --> 00:10:20,500
When I finish my exams,
we'll have another party.

163
00:10:20,540 --> 00:10:21,500
Take care, yeah?

164
00:10:21,540 --> 00:10:22,500
All right.

165
00:10:22,540 --> 00:10:24,460
You be nice to Mum.

166
00:10:24,500 --> 00:10:25,820
Yeah. See you in a bit.

167
00:10:36,340 --> 00:10:38,540
Emma, what are you doing
out here?

168
00:10:38,580 --> 00:10:40,500
They're waiting for you inside.
Come on.

169
00:10:40,500 --> 00:10:41,940
Okay, yeah. Okay.

170
00:10:54,100 --> 00:10:55,740
Okay.

171
00:10:55,780 --> 00:10:58,820
Can I have your French homework,
please?

172
00:10:58,860 --> 00:11:00,420
<i>Oui, professeur.</i>

173
00:11:00,460 --> 00:11:03,260
<i>Oui professeur.</i>

174
00:11:08,380 --> 00:11:09,580
Fine, Mark.

175
00:11:09,620 --> 00:11:10,580
Emma.

176
00:11:17,260 --> 00:11:18,700
Why isn't it finished?

177
00:11:18,740 --> 00:11:21,340
Emma, you can't keep using
the excuse of your hand...

178
00:11:21,380 --> 00:11:26,340
I have to go
to the bathroom.

179
00:12:25,500 --> 00:12:26,900
Sis?

180
00:12:26,900 --> 00:12:29,220
Haven't you been taught
to knock?

181
00:12:29,260 --> 00:12:30,740
The door was open.

182
00:12:30,780 --> 00:12:33,660
It's my fault, then,
I suppose.

183
00:12:33,700 --> 00:12:35,660
Well, what is it now?

184
00:12:35,700 --> 00:12:36,900
You were writing
on the mirror,

185
00:12:36,940 --> 00:12:39,340
and your eyes were...

186
00:12:39,380 --> 00:12:42,980
It freaked me out.

187
00:12:43,020 --> 00:12:45,140
Oh, get lost, you creep.

188
00:13:04,020 --> 00:13:06,100
Happy birthday, cous.

189
00:13:06,140 --> 00:13:08,020
I have a little prezzie for ya.

190
00:13:08,020 --> 00:13:09,380
Enjoy.

191
00:13:29,300 --> 00:13:30,260
Emma?

192
00:13:30,300 --> 00:13:31,260
Yeah?

193
00:13:31,300 --> 00:13:32,460
I need to talk to you.

194
00:13:32,500 --> 00:13:34,140
Can you come down to my study
for a minute?

195
00:13:35,100 --> 00:13:36,540
Yeah, I'm coming.

196
00:13:43,380 --> 00:13:45,300
Emma.

197
00:13:50,980 --> 00:13:52,900
What's wrong?

198
00:13:54,660 --> 00:13:57,100
What?

199
00:13:57,140 --> 00:13:59,100
If I tell you, you have to
promise you won't tell Alex.

200
00:13:59,140 --> 00:14:01,180
Yeah.

201
00:14:01,220 --> 00:14:04,300
My parents are taking me
to see a psychologist.

202
00:14:04,340 --> 00:14:06,220
Is that all?

203
00:14:06,260 --> 00:14:09,980
Emma, loads of kids at my school
see psychologists.

204
00:14:10,020 --> 00:14:12,020
It's fine.

205
00:14:12,060 --> 00:14:13,460
But the thing is,

206
00:14:13,460 --> 00:14:15,820
the guy that they're sending me
to see is, like, a freak.

207
00:14:15,860 --> 00:14:16,860
Why?

208
00:14:16,900 --> 00:14:18,380
He hypnotizes people.

209
00:14:18,420 --> 00:14:20,620
What if I tell him about
all the dodgy stuff I get up to,

210
00:14:20,660 --> 00:14:22,380
and I don't even
realize it, like?

211
00:14:22,420 --> 00:14:25,220
Look, we can easily find
a solution for that,

212
00:14:25,260 --> 00:14:28,580
if you want.

213
00:14:31,220 --> 00:14:33,260
All right, well,
I'm just going to dim

214
00:14:33,300 --> 00:14:34,740
the lights a little bit.

215
00:14:34,780 --> 00:14:36,940
There.

216
00:14:36,980 --> 00:14:38,020
That's much better.

217
00:14:38,060 --> 00:14:39,140
Good.

218
00:14:40,460 --> 00:14:45,020
Now we can start.

219
00:14:45,060 --> 00:14:49,540
Now, if there's anything that
you don't want to talk about,

220
00:14:49,580 --> 00:14:52,780
you're under no obligation
to do so.

221
00:14:52,820 --> 00:14:56,180
What I want is that
you feel relaxed.

222
00:14:56,220 --> 00:14:58,380
All right.

223
00:14:58,420 --> 00:15:02,940
Your parents tell me
that they teach you at home

224
00:15:02,980 --> 00:15:06,340
but that you would
really rather go

225
00:15:06,380 --> 00:15:08,420
to the secondary school
with teenagers your own age.

226
00:15:08,460 --> 00:15:09,500
Is that right?

227
00:15:09,540 --> 00:15:12,340
Yeah, that's right.

228
00:15:12,380 --> 00:15:14,940
Are you comfortable?

229
00:15:14,980 --> 00:15:16,620
<i>Yeah.</i>

230
00:15:16,660 --> 00:15:19,260
<i>Your hand...
does it hurt?</i>

231
00:15:19,300 --> 00:15:21,620
<i>Not anymore.</i>

232
00:15:21,660 --> 00:15:24,140
Exactly what happened?

233
00:15:24,180 --> 00:15:27,020
I slipped in the bathroom

234
00:15:27,060 --> 00:15:28,500
and knocked over
the mirror and cut my...

235
00:15:28,540 --> 00:15:30,540
cut myself with it.

236
00:15:39,300 --> 00:15:41,620
Emma?

237
00:15:41,660 --> 00:15:43,580
Emma, are you okay?

238
00:15:47,100 --> 00:15:48,780
Yeah.

239
00:15:48,820 --> 00:15:50,420
Sorry.

240
00:15:50,460 --> 00:15:52,540
Good.

241
00:15:52,580 --> 00:15:54,180
Now, what I want you to do

242
00:15:54,220 --> 00:15:58,300
is to concentrate
on my finger.

243
00:15:58,340 --> 00:15:59,780
Okay?

244
00:15:59,820 --> 00:16:01,820
Concentrate.

245
00:16:01,860 --> 00:16:03,780
Look at my finger.

246
00:16:03,820 --> 00:16:06,260
Look at it.

247
00:16:06,300 --> 00:16:08,060
That's it.

248
00:16:08,100 --> 00:16:10,300
Start relaxing.

249
00:16:11,580 --> 00:16:14,220
<i>Your heartbeat slows down.</i>

250
00:16:14,260 --> 00:16:17,220
<i>And it's slowing down.</i>

251
00:16:17,260 --> 00:16:18,660
<i>That's good.</i>

252
00:16:18,700 --> 00:16:21,860
Your arms are heavy.

253
00:16:21,900 --> 00:16:24,260
Your eyelids are heavy.

254
00:16:24,300 --> 00:16:26,740
Your heart is slowing.

255
00:16:26,780 --> 00:16:29,620
Good.

256
00:16:29,660 --> 00:16:32,060
Your arms are heavy.

257
00:16:32,100 --> 00:16:35,460
You need to sleep.

258
00:16:37,780 --> 00:16:41,260
Good.

259
00:16:51,740 --> 00:16:55,420
Would you say
that you are happy, Emma?

260
00:16:55,460 --> 00:16:57,180
<i> Have you ever
taken drugs, Emma?</i>

261
00:16:57,220 --> 00:16:58,580
<i>Have you had sex yet, Emma?</i>

262
00:16:58,580 --> 00:16:59,980
<i>Do you do everything
your told, Emma?</i>

263
00:17:00,020 --> 00:17:01,420
Emma?

264
00:17:01,460 --> 00:17:02,660
Emma?

265
00:17:06,900 --> 00:17:09,420
<i>- Emma, wake up.
- Emma's not going to wake up.</i>

266
00:17:41,180 --> 00:17:42,980
How are you doing?

267
00:17:46,660 --> 00:17:52,700
What happened today,
it wasn't your fault.

268
00:17:52,740 --> 00:17:55,780
You know that, don't you?

269
00:18:08,380 --> 00:18:11,500
If you want to talk about it...

270
00:18:11,540 --> 00:18:12,940
or anything...

271
00:18:32,700 --> 00:18:35,820
But, Emma, your voice.

272
00:18:35,860 --> 00:18:38,060
The guy had a heart attack
because of what you said.

273
00:18:38,100 --> 00:18:40,820
You went straight
