but I'll come and see you
tomorrow morning.

810
00:55:47,300 --> 00:55:48,820
Okay?

811
00:56:06,420 --> 00:56:07,900
I'm not hungry.

812
00:56:07,940 --> 00:56:09,020
You have to eat.

813
00:56:09,060 --> 00:56:10,980
We need you to be strong.

814
00:56:21,580 --> 00:56:22,740
Don't worry, Father.

815
00:56:22,780 --> 00:56:24,740
I'm not going
to starve to death.

816
00:56:24,780 --> 00:56:26,620
I'm not like that other girl.

817
00:56:26,660 --> 00:56:28,860
<i>Padre, no deje que me lleven.</i>

818
00:56:28,900 --> 00:56:29,860
<i>Padre.</i>

819
00:56:29,900 --> 00:56:31,780
Silence, Demon.

820
00:56:31,820 --> 00:56:33,260
Take it easy, Father.

821
00:56:33,300 --> 00:56:35,140
We're together forever.

822
00:56:39,700 --> 00:56:40,860
John.

823
00:56:40,900 --> 00:56:43,740
Are you sure Mark's your son?

824
00:56:43,780 --> 00:56:45,620
You did everything you could
to make sure

825
00:56:45,660 --> 00:56:47,340
Lucy didn't get pregnant again,
and yet...

826
00:56:48,500 --> 00:56:49,820
Do you remember Steve?

827
00:56:49,860 --> 00:56:55,340
Lucy's colleague,
who was so good-looking?

828
00:57:06,540 --> 00:57:07,940
You all right?

829
00:57:10,340 --> 00:57:11,380
What happened?

830
00:57:11,420 --> 00:57:14,340
Nothing.
Nothing happened.

831
00:57:16,900 --> 00:57:19,020
I'm gonna go to my room.

832
00:57:53,940 --> 00:57:58,340
It's the first time
that... this thing

833
00:57:58,380 --> 00:58:00,820
has shown itself
outside the room, right?

834
00:58:07,700 --> 00:58:09,580
It's getting stronger,
isn't it?

835
00:58:11,380 --> 00:58:13,660
I'm going to bring
somebody else in.

836
00:58:13,700 --> 00:58:15,740
I've been overconfident.

837
00:58:15,780 --> 00:58:18,700
I can't do it alone.

838
00:58:18,740 --> 00:58:20,820
Who are you going to call in?

839
00:58:20,860 --> 00:58:22,460
Father Ennis.

840
00:58:22,500 --> 00:58:25,540
He's my old mentor.

841
00:58:25,580 --> 00:58:26,860
He's in Rome, though,

842
00:58:26,900 --> 00:58:30,820
so it'll be a few days
before he can get here.

843
00:58:30,860 --> 00:58:32,260
By the way,

844
00:58:32,300 --> 00:58:36,740
I've already told Emma,
but it's important

845
00:58:36,780 --> 00:58:40,740
that you and Lucie
should know this too.

846
00:58:40,780 --> 00:58:43,980
You must make sure that Emma
is never alone with anyone.

847
00:58:46,540 --> 00:58:48,620
And another thing.

848
00:58:48,660 --> 00:58:51,940
You must forget everything
you heard just now.

849
00:58:51,980 --> 00:58:52,940
But what she said...

850
00:58:52,980 --> 00:58:55,020
The Devil always lies.

851
00:58:55,060 --> 00:58:56,620
Always.

852
00:58:59,220 --> 00:59:03,180
You can't allow him to use you
for his purposes.

853
00:59:14,380 --> 00:59:17,780
Well, I say good night, then.

854
00:59:17,820 --> 00:59:19,500
Good night.

855
00:59:31,380 --> 00:59:32,900
- Leave me alone.
- Please, please.

856
00:59:32,980 --> 00:59:34,100
Lucy, please.

857
00:59:34,140 --> 00:59:36,580
You think it's been easy
to say that?

858
00:59:36,620 --> 00:59:38,140
You're accusing me
of having an affair.

859
00:59:38,180 --> 00:59:39,460
How am I supposed
to react to that?

860
00:59:39,500 --> 00:59:40,740
Look, please, just believe me.

861
00:59:40,780 --> 00:59:42,420
It's not easy to say,

862
00:59:42,460 --> 00:59:44,580
but it's something that was said
the other day by Emma.

863
00:59:44,620 --> 00:59:46,380
Yeah, but she's not very well
at the moment.

864
00:59:46,420 --> 00:59:48,900
But if I didn't say something,
then I'd be thinking about this.

865
00:59:48,940 --> 00:59:50,820
That he's not your son.

866
00:59:50,860 --> 00:59:52,660
How can you even think

867
00:59:52,700 --> 00:59:54,220
that such a thing
could be true?

868
00:59:54,260 --> 00:59:55,660
I'm not gonna take
any kind of tests.

869
01:01:24,340 --> 01:01:25,700
Hi.

870
01:01:25,740 --> 01:01:27,420
- Hi.
- How are you?

871
01:01:27,460 --> 01:01:28,900
Is Auntie looking after you
all right?

872
01:01:28,980 --> 01:01:29,900
Yes.

873
01:01:29,940 --> 01:01:31,180
That ball's mine.

874
01:01:31,180 --> 01:01:32,380
Can I have it back?

875
01:01:32,420 --> 01:01:33,620
And what will I get
in exchange?

876
01:01:33,660 --> 01:01:34,620
A kiss?

877
01:01:44,340 --> 01:01:46,220
If I'm not getting anything
in return,

878
01:01:46,260 --> 01:01:48,140
I think I might keep it.

879
01:01:48,180 --> 01:01:49,740
That ball's mine.

880
01:01:49,780 --> 01:01:51,180
Dad gave it to me.

881
01:01:57,060 --> 01:01:58,340
Get lost!

882
01:01:58,380 --> 01:02:00,220
I'm going to tell Auntie.

883
01:02:00,260 --> 01:02:01,660
Catch!

884
01:02:04,100 --> 01:02:06,060
You're stupid!

885
01:02:11,540 --> 01:02:14,020
Mark. Where are you going?

886
01:02:14,060 --> 01:02:15,340
Come back.

887
01:02:15,340 --> 01:02:17,580
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

888
01:04:02,060 --> 01:04:03,020
Hi.

889
01:04:03,060 --> 01:04:04,180
Rose.

890
01:04:04,220 --> 01:04:07,020
I...

891
01:04:08,700 --> 01:04:10,620
Let's go, Mum.

892
01:04:29,420 --> 01:04:32,900
It's all my fault.

893
01:04:32,940 --> 01:04:34,220
I killed him.

894
01:04:35,700 --> 01:04:37,660
Can I tell my mom
the truth?

895
01:04:37,700 --> 01:04:39,460
It's too late for the truth.

896
01:04:39,500 --> 01:04:42,380
It wasn't your fault.

897
01:04:42,420 --> 01:04:43,580
I should just kill myself.

898
01:04:43,620 --> 01:04:45,140
That's what I should do.

899
01:04:45,180 --> 01:04:47,980
Hey.

900
01:04:48,020 --> 01:04:50,100
Apart from anything else,

901
01:04:50,140 --> 01:04:53,060
you'd be condemning
your soul to Hell.

902
01:04:53,100 --> 01:04:55,100
That's a victory for the Devil.

903
01:04:56,780 --> 01:05:01,060
You can't let Mark's death
have been for nothing.

904
01:05:01,100 --> 01:05:02,540
Come.

905
01:06:18,540 --> 01:06:20,140
Mum, are you there?

906
01:06:21,580 --> 01:06:23,620
I need to tell you
something that...

907
01:06:23,660 --> 01:06:26,820
that I should have
told you before.

908
01:06:26,860 --> 01:06:29,300
It's all my fault, Mum.

909
01:06:29,340 --> 01:06:32,260
All of it.

910
01:06:40,020 --> 01:06:44,540
One day, I went to visit Uncle
in the canteen, and...

911
01:06:44,580 --> 01:06:46,260
I told him that I had played
on the Ouija board.

912
01:06:46,300 --> 01:06:47,580
Why did you want to do that?

913
01:06:47,620 --> 01:06:50,340
I don't know.

914
01:06:50,380 --> 01:06:51,740
I thought he'd get angry.

915
01:06:51,780 --> 01:06:55,660
He just laughed instead
and said that invoking the devil

916
01:06:55,700 --> 01:06:57,460
wasn't as easy as it seemed

917
01:06:57,500 --> 01:06:59,260
and that playing
with the Ouija board

918
01:06:59,300 --> 01:07:00,940
just... just wasn't enough.

919
01:07:00,940 --> 01:07:03,180
I thought that's what you do,
though, with the Ouija board,

920
01:07:03,220 --> 01:07:05,100
because it's supposed
to invoked spirits, yeah?

921
01:07:05,140 --> 01:07:07,540
Well, spirits
but not the Devil.

922
01:07:07,580 --> 01:07:09,020
I mean, in order
to invoke the devil,

923
01:07:09,060 --> 01:07:10,900
you need to make
a blood sacrifice.

924
01:07:13,100 --> 01:07:14,460
Sacrifice?

925
01:07:14,500 --> 01:07:16,060
Their own blood?

926
01:07:16,100 --> 01:07:17,740
I'll show you.

927
01:07:17,780 --> 01:07:22,180
Uncle Chris knows
a lot about it.

928
01:07:22,220 --> 01:07:26,180
He has loads of stuff
about the Devil in his flat.

929
01:07:31,260 --> 01:07:35,340
He showed me how the girl
who died did it.

930
01:07:35,340 --> 01:07:38,220
Ana invoked the Devil
using this pentagram.

931
01:07:38,220 --> 01:07:40,020
She drew it with her own blood.

932
01:07:40,060 --> 01:07:41,420
I pretended not
to be interested,

933
01:07:41,460 --> 01:07:44,620
but I memorized it.

934
01:07:44,620 --> 01:07:46,500
I memorized it all.

935
01:07:46,540 --> 01:07:52,420
The night of my birthday,
I played on it again.

936
01:07:52,460 --> 01:07:54,220
Oh, spirit, if you are there,
give us a sign.

937
01:07:54,220 --> 01:07:55,500
Uncle was right.

938
01:07:55,500 --> 01:07:57,220
It was a waste of time.

939
01:07:57,260 --> 01:07:59,980
But that night,
when I came home,

940
01:08:00,020 --> 01:08:01,540
you were waiting up for me.

941
01:08:01,580 --> 01:08:02,740
Where the hell have you been?

942
01:08:02,780 --> 01:08:06,220
Do you realize what time it is?

943
01:08:06,260 --> 01:08:07,500
You realized I was drunk,

944
01:08:07,540 --> 01:08:08,940
and you shouted at me.

945
01:08:08,940 --> 01:08:10,140
You find it funny?

946
01:08:10,180 --> 01:08:12,220
You will not leave your room
for the next month.

947
01:08:12,260 --> 01:08:13,660
You will stay in,
you will study,

948
01:08:13,700 --> 01:08:16,460
and there will be no allowance,
no friends, nothing.

949
01:08:16,500 --> 01:08:20,740
I... hate you so much.

950
01:08:20,780 --> 01:08:21,700
Aah.

951
01:08:21,740 --> 01:08:23,380
Get to bed!

952
01:08:23,420 --> 01:08:25,420
Get to bed now!

953
01:08:28,380 --> 01:08:31,020
Mum...

954
01:08:32,260 --> 01:08:34,380
I've never been so angry.

955
01:08:34,420 --> 01:08:38,140
I got really, really angry.

956
01:08:40,140 --> 01:08:42,620
What happened after that,

957
01:08:42,660 --> 01:08:47,220
well, it wasn't an accident.

958
01:08:47,260 --> 01:08:49,300
I didn't slip in the bathroom.

959
01:08:51,100 --> 01:08:52,380
I did it on purpose.

960
01:08:52,420 --> 01:08:55,660
I cut myself because...

961
01:08:55,660 --> 01:08:57,660
because I wanted to.

962
01:09:20,340 --> 01:09:22,940
I started to draw
the pentagram.

963
01:09:22,980 --> 01:09:25,380
And just... just like
that girl did.

964
01:09:27,780 --> 01:09:30,060
And it worked.

965
01:09:30,060 --> 01:09:34,220
And I felt that something
took over my body.

966
01:09:35,380 --> 01:09:39,020
He... he asked me
what I wanted.

967
01:09:42,500 --> 01:09:46,180
I want to be free.

968
01:09:47,140 --> 01:09:50,660
I want to be free.

969
01:09:50,700 --> 01:09:54,060
I told him I wanted to be free,

970
01:09:54,100 --> 01:09:56,780
especially
free from my family.

971
01:09:58,700 --> 01:10:01,740
But I didn't know it would be
like this, Mum.

972
01:10:01,780 --> 01:10:05,340
I didn't even believe in...
the Devil existed.

973
01:10:05,380 --> 01:10:07,180
I'm so sorry.

974
01:10:09,820 --> 01:10:12,620
Mum, say something.

975
01:10:12,620 --> 01:10:14,740
Mum, please say something.

976
01:10:14,780 --> 01:10:20,580
Say anything.
Just please say something.

977
01:10:24,780 --> 01:10:29,060
Please.

978
01:10:56,620 --> 01:10:58,060
Mum.

979
01:11:00,900 --> 01:11:02,700
What are you doing?

980
01:11:03,780 --> 01:11:05,180
Mum, what are you doing?

981
01:11:06,660 --> 01:11:07,740
Mum!

982
01:11:07,780 --> 01:11:09,300
Mum!
What are you doing?

983
01:11:09,340 --> 01:11:10,300
Mum!

984
01:11:10,340 --> 01:11:11,980
What are you doing?

985
01:11:11,980 --> 01:11:13,220
Mum.

986
01:11:17,420 --> 01:11:22,220
Please stop.
What are you doing?

987
01:11:22,260 --> 01:11:24,820
Mum, please.

988
01:11:24,860 --> 01:11:26,100
What's wrong?

989
01:11:26,140 --> 01:11:27,380
Mum, look at me, please.

990
01:11:27,420 --> 01:11:29,340
What's wrong?

991
01:11:31,820 --> 01:11:32,860
Mum.

992
01:11:32,900 --> 01:11:34,820
Mum!

993
01:11:36,180 --> 01:11:37,660
Where are you going?

994
01:11:37,700 --> 01:11:39,860
I'm so sorry.

995
01:11:40,820 --> 01:11:43,500
I'm so sorry.

996
01:11:43,500 --> 01:11:45,780
Please forgive me.

997
01:11:45,820 --> 01:11:47,660
Please forgive me!

998
01:11:49,860 --> 01:11:51,940
Mum. Mum.

999
01:11:51,980 --> 01:11:53,340
Mum, no!

1000
01:11:53,380 --> 01:11:54,660
Mum, no!

1001
01:11:56,260 --> 01:11:58,980
Mum!

1002
01:12:08,300 --> 01:12:11,380
Mum, Mum, you're all right.

1003
01:12:11,420 --> 01:12:14,300
You're all right.
You're okay.

1004
01:12:15,900 --> 01:12:17,060
Can you hear me sweetheart?

1005
01:12:17,100 --> 01:12:18,780
Sarah's coming
to the hospital with you.

1006
01:12:18,820 --> 01:12:21,060
I'll come as soon as I can,
all right?

1007
01:12:51,980 --> 01:12:53,740
Father Ennis.

1008
01:12:53,780 --> 01:12:55,860
It... it's Christopher.

1009
01:12:55,900 --> 01:12:58,460
Did you get my message?

1010
01:13:00,380 --> 01:13:01,660
Please. You must come.

1011
01:13:01,700 --> 01:13:05,100
It's very...

1012
01:13:05,140 --> 01:13:08,260
I beg your pardon.
Monsignor.

1013
01:13:08,300 --> 01:13:10,300
I forgot.

1014
01:13:16,060 --> 01:13:18,500
Good morning.

1015
01:13:18,540 --> 01:13:19,980
I'm going back to the hospital,

1016
01:13:20,020 --> 01:13:22,580
take some things to Mum.

1017
01:13:23,700 --> 01:13:25,020
How is she?

1018
01:13:25,060 --> 01:13:26,220
She's resting.

1019
01:13:27,260 --> 01:13:28,660
Can I come with you?

1020
01:13:28,700 --> 01:13:31,140
No. It's better you don't.

1021
01:13:31,180 --> 01:13:32,940
Christopher will be down soon.

1022
01:13:32,980 --> 01:13:35,300
If anything happens, he'll...
he'll take you to the hospital.

1023
01:13:37,660 --> 01:13:39,260
I'll see you later.

1024
01:13:42,820 --> 01:13:44,420
Hi, Chris.

1025
01:13:44,460 --> 01:13:46,900
I'm going to the hospital
to take some things for Lucy.

1026
01:13:46,940 --> 01:13:48,460
How are you doing?

1027
01:13:48,500 --> 01:13:50,460
Well, tired,
but I'll be all right.

1028
01:13:50,500 --> 01:13:53,100
- Give her my love.
- Okay, will do.

1029
01:13:53,100 --> 01:13:56,100
I'll see you later.

1030
01:13:56,140 --> 01:13:58,180
Hi.

1031
01:13:58,220 --> 01:13:59,300
How are you doing?

1032
01:14:10,060 --> 01:14:15,540
Emma, your mum's gonna be fine,
you know?

1033
01:14:15,580 --> 01:14:17,020
God won't...

1034
01:14:17,060 --> 01:14:18,980
Let anything bad happen
to her, I know.

1035
01:14:19,020 --> 01:14:22,780
You told me the same
in the hospital.

1036
01:14:22,820 --> 01:14:26,860
I'm not going to carry on
doing the exorcisms.

1037
01:14:26,860 --> 01:14:28,460
Emma.

1038
01:14:28,500 --> 01:14:30,660
If it hasn't worked so far,

1039
01:14:30,700 --> 01:14:33,060
what makes you think
that it'll work now, like?

1040
01:14:33,100 --> 01:14:34,540
I can't do any more.

1041
01:14:34,580 --> 01:14:35,700
Emma, please.

1042
01:14:35,740 --> 01:14:37,220
Uh-uh.

1043
01:14:37,260 --> 01:14:39,780
I'm going to ask my dad
to put me in

1044
01:14:39,820 --> 01:14:42,340
a psychiatric hospital
or something.

1045
01:14:42,380 --> 01:14:44,260
You're not mad, sweetheart.

1046
01:14:44,300 --> 01:14:45,460
No?

1047
01:14:45,500 --> 01:14:48,780
I see insects
that aren't really there.

1048
01:14:48,780 --> 01:14:51,900
I hear voices in my head,

1049
01:14:51,940 --> 01:14:54,100
and I kind of caused everything
that has happened.

1050
01:14:54,140 --> 01:14:56,220
If you'd seen
what I've seen...

1051
01:14:56,260 --> 01:14:58,500
Well maybe that's it,
because I haven't seen anything.

1052
01:15:00,220 --> 01:15:02,820
I want to see the tapes.

1053
01:15:02,860 --> 01:15:03,900
All of them.

1054
01:15:03,940 --> 01:15:06,060
No, I can't.

1055
01:15:06,060 --> 01:15:07,820
It'd be too painful for you.

1056
01:15:07,860 --> 01:15:11,300
In that case, forget it.

1057
01:15:11,340 --> 01:15:14,460
Listen to me, please.

1058
01:15:14,500 --> 01:15:15,820
I've asked another priest
for help.

1059
01:15:15,860 --> 01:15:17,180
He'll be here
in a couple of days,

1060
01:15:17,220 --> 01:15:19,620
and between the two of us,
we will be able to help you.

1061
01:15:19,660 --> 01:15:20,980
I don't care.

1062
01:15:21,020 --> 01:15:24,500
Emma, think
of your mum and dad.

1063
01:15:24,540 --> 01:15:25,740
You can't give up.

1064
01:15:25,780 --> 01:15:27,860
Are you going
to show me those tapes?

1065
01:15:27,900 --> 01:15:29,700
No.

1066
01:16:05,740 --> 01:16:07,100
Sorry about earlier.

1067
01:16:07,140 --> 01:16:11,620
I didn't mean to be rude
or offensive.

1068
01:16:11,660 --> 01:16:14,260
Don't worry about it.

1069
01:16:14,300 --> 01:16:16,220
I'm going to my room.

1070
01:17:28,980 --> 01:17:30,620
<i>Everlasting God.</i>

1071
01:17:30,660 --> 01:17:32,620
<i>I don't understand you,
priest!</i>

1072
01:17:32,660 --> 01:17:33,820
<i>Silence!</i>

1073
01:17:33,860 --> 01:17:34,820
<i>Be quiet, or I swear...</i>

1074
01:17:34,860 --> 01:17:36,980
<i>You'll do what?</i>

1075
01:17:37,020 --> 01:17:40,900
<i>You're not doing anything
to let me leave this body.</i>

1076
01:17:42,700 --> 01:17:45,180
<i>What do you want exactly,
little priestling?</i>

